1. Hadoop file system - hdfs can be accessed using
  hadoop fs -ls [ finding all the files in hdfs]

2. hadoop configuration can be found in /etc/hadoop/conf

3. Check the health of hadoop directory we can use
hadoop fsck {folder_name}

4. we can check a folder in hadoop using
hadoop fs -ls {path to FOLDER in hadoop}

hadoop fs -ls /user/venkat1992/data_import/retail_db

5. hadoop file system we can see the contents in a file using `tail`

hadoop fs -tail {path to FILE in haoop}

  
